Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Regarding the security situation, Mohamed Belahcen, 
an official responsible for religious affairs in Ain Defla 
Province, was assassinated yesterday after the Friday prayers. 
The victim was 62 years old and was the imam of the Ghinali 
mosque in Medea. 
  Six civilians were assassinated last week in El Tarf, Oum El 
Bouaghi, and Mostaganem provinces. In El Tarf Province, three 
militants of the FLN [National Liberation Front] were 
assassinated with knives on the night of 2 January after the 
hunting rifles in their possession were taken from them. 
  In Oum El Bouaghi Province, the first deputy chairman of the 
executive authority of the (Ouled Hamda) municipality was 
assassinated the day before yesterday. Also the day before 
yesterday, in Mostaganem Province a retired health service 
employee was assassinated at the exit of the mosque in the town 
of Mostaganem. 
  Meanwhile the security authorities said that they had killed 
four members of armed gangs and had arrested four others in the 
center and east of the country. 

